Ad Text:
About us   

At Healthdirect Australia we work with purpose and dedication to help Australians actively manage and improve their health.

Our virtual services are easily accessible via multiple channels, including helplines, video call solutions and websites and cater for Australians at all stages of life. No matter where people live, or what time of the day or night it is, they can use our services to talk to a health professional, find trusted information and advice online and locate their closest health service.
  
About the opportunity

Reporting to the General Manager Strategy & CX, you will lead the design, delivery and continuous improvement of our consumer survey programs, using a VOC platform to capture feedback, surface insights and drive tangible action across the organisation. You’ll partner closely with service teams and cross‑divisional stakeholders to embed consumer‑centric decision‑making and track the impact of improvements over time.
  
Key Responsibilities:

Lead quantitative and qualitative survey design, testing, programming and deployment in a VOC platform (e.g., Qualtrics, Forsta). Establish robust sampling frameworks and complete pre‑testing before launch.
Conduct rigorous analysis; translate findings into actionable insights, risk flags and recommendations. Produce high‑quality visualisations and reports that meet contract and quality requirements.
Facilitate multidisciplinary insights reviews; maintain an insights action register and trace improvements through to implementation. Present to senior leadership and partners.
Support internal users to self‑serve ad‑hoc analysis in the VOC platform; champion best‑practice methods, tools and dashboards. Ensure compliance with privacy, ethics and data handling.
Work within the Quality, Safety & Experience Division to unite clinical governance with consumer expectations and guide innovation in digital and virtual care.
What You’ll Bring

Proven experience leading large‑scale survey programs and sampling methodologies.
Hands‑on expertise with VOC platforms (e.g., Qualtrics, Forsta or equivalent).
Advanced analytical and storytelling skills—able to distil complex findings into compelling narratives that influence senior decision‑making.
Strong stakeholder engagement across multidisciplinary teams.
Degree in Public Health, Social Sciences, Market Research, Statistics or related discipline; 7+ years in research insights & analytics.
Why work with us

We believe our strength comes from our talented and dedicated staff. We are committed to working together to create a culture where you can bring your whole self to work.
  
Our benefits include:

Flexible work arrangements (2 days per week in office, pro-rated for part time employees).
14 weeks company Paid Parental Leave for both parents.
Multi-dimensional wellbeing program that is run by our people for our people.
Individual curated learner journeys to support you to expand your capabilities and unlock your talent.
To find out more about Healthdirect, and our vision for a healthier Australia, please visit our website - about.healthdirect.gov.au.
  
As an Equal Opportunity Employer, we respect and seek to empower each individual, and support the diverse cultures, perspectives, skills, and experiences within our workforce. 

Click Apply to submit your application for this role. Please be aware that you must have the right to live and work in Australia to apply for this job.

Job description:


Build data foundations for personalisation at scale.
Work on BigQuery in Google Cloud Platform and Adobe AEP on a greenfield project.
Make an impact on high-profile, business-critical initiatives.

The opportunity to join our team

We have an exciting opportunity for a Data Engineer to join the team on a 12-month contract. In this role you will work with cutting-edge technology like Adobe Experience Platform and Google Cloud on a greenfield project that is backed by executive sponsorship. You will play a key role in a top-priority initiative, contributing to big projects that shape the future of personalised customer engagement. Expect mentoring and development opportunities alongside senior experts, and the chance to make a real impact, not just BAU work, but meaningful contributions that deliver value to the business and our customers.

This role will help to architect and automate the foundational data assets that power personalised customer experiences. You will play a key role in setting up our data products in UDP and ensuring smooth operations after the transition. This is a hands-on technical role where you will partner with Marketing, IT, Digital, and Data teams to deliver scalable solutions for lifecycle campaigns, segmentation, and predictive modelling while navigating regulatory sensitivities in a trust-centric sector.

Key areas of this role include:

Build and maintain scalable data models and marts in Google BigQuery
Write efficient, well-structured SQL for transformations, aggregations, and reporting
Deliver data assets that enable personalised journeys including onboarding, retention, upsell, and win-back campaigns
Collaborate with Data Science teams to operationalise segmentation and predictive models
Partner cross-functionally to translate business needs into technical solutions
Ensure data quality, governance, and compliance with privacy standards
Document processes and champion best practices for long-term sustainability


What You Bring to This Role
We are seeking someone who combines strong technical skills with the ability to collaborate effectively across teams.

Experience in data engineering (marketing data assets preferred)
Experience in building scalable and reusable data products from raw unstructured data
Strong SQL skills and hands-on experience with Google Cloud Platform(GCP) & Google BigQuery is a must
Exposure to Adobe Experience Platform or similar CDPs is desirable
Familiarity with Python and data orchestration tools such as dbt or Airflow
Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills
Self-starter, quick learner, and comfortable working close to technical execution
Understanding of data privacy frameworks and compliance in regulated industries

Job Title: Head of AI Product – Search, Recommendations, Personalisation
Ad Text:
Company Description

About SEEK

At SEEK, we serve a noble purpose: to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and to help organisations succeed.

By joining us, you’ll be part of a multi-national technology business that is far-reaching with a start-up working culture that focuses on a set of collaborative values and appreciates dynamic cultures. SEEK is a place where potential meets possibility – it’s where your career aspiration and our purpose can make great things happen.

Why join us?

Be part of a multi-national tech company with strong core values to help us solve complex challenges for our customers while building a flexible, exciting career – one that could take you anywhere.

We’re looking for people who thrive in dynamic teams and enjoy tackling regular new challenges in a large-scale, modern, and agile environment. As one of Asia Pacific’s largest tech companies, you’ll contribute to multi-lingual systems, solving high-impact problems to the benefit of millions of people within the region.

Be part of a fast-growing company with a strong culture and clear purpose, innovation and strong investment in responsible AI. SEEK offers you the opportunity to be involved in impactful work and be part of a great team. Expect a great investment in your career development with access to workshops, conferences and courses while you work alongside seasoned experts.

Job Description

About the role

As Head of AI Product for Search, Recommendations and Personalisation, you will lead a team of AI Product Managers responsible for defining and executing our AI product strategy across a candidate's career discovery journey.

AI products at SEEK are developed by cross-functional teams of AI Product Managers, Data Scientists and Engineers, working together to define, build, test and scale AI solutions for our most important and complex customer and business problems. You will work closely with Data Science and Engineering leaders to guide three AI squads, namely Search, Recommendations and Personalisation. These three squads are collectively referred to as Career Discovery, and power how candidates discover their next career opportunity.

In this role, you will define, align and communicate the Career Discovery ambition, which connects to SEEK's strategy and candidate needs and identifies opportunities to unlock value through AI and data. You will represent the SEEK AI team with senior stakeholders across Product, Strategy, Commercial and Sales, influencing the company's broader strategy, product ambitions and roadmaps.

Responsibilities

Align with technical co-leaders of the Search, Recommendations and Personalisation AI problem domain to articulate a strategy, ambition and compelling vision. The ambition needs to bring together a deep understanding of the current and future customer opportunities, SEEK’s strategy and product ambitions, and how to unlock value using AI and data.
Lead AI Product Managers to build a deep understanding of customer needs, met, unmet, stated and unstated, and product partners’ strategies and priorities.
Focus teams on solving critical customer problems of high strategic and commercial importance, informed by a variety of customer immersion, quant and qual methodologies.
Drive an overall roadmap for the problem domain that articulates what we need to do to achieve our ambition over a  3–5-year horizon.  Includes articulating resource and investment needs for the domain and achieving buy in from key stakeholders & partners on the sequencing and resourcing for the roadmap.
Coach teams to collaborate with partner product teams, SEEK strategy and technical teams to solve problems and drive effective decisions: defining ambiguous problem spaces, framing options and trade-offs.
Work with other AI leaders to set expectations for and support teams to design analytical and technical solutions, including MVP services and experiments to validate the solution and iterate quickly. Drive a culture and practice of experimentation that focuses on clear business goals, linked metrics and best practice experimentation methodology.
Own the performance of your product portfolio by defining success metrics with partners, creating a data driven understanding of performance and how it supports the broader marketplace. Build a culture where domain teams monitor product, competitive, market and technical metrics, identifying issues and prioritising product improvements.
Ensure the delivery of the roadmap by aligning senior stakeholders around priorities and resourcing, guiding teams to set and deliver the right quarterly objectives, and helping remove roadblocks for teams.
Hire, inspire and lead a high performing team. Coach and support team members to continuously improve their product practice. Create a culture and environment that empowers teams to deliver and innovate.
Qualifications

Essential Qualifications, Skills and Experience

Proven track record of developing and communicating a clear strategy, distilling complex concepts into simple, clear frameworks and guidance
Strong experience leading and empowering high performing product teams to deliver customer outcomes
Commercial acumen and a sound grasp of mathematics and analytical concepts, including the ability to break down product and commercial performance into clear drivers and present insights effectively
High learning orientation, with an interest in the latest AI concepts and the ability to stay current with industry trends in a rapidly changing environment

Other Qualifications, Skills and Experience

Experience in online marketplaces
Excellent communication and influencing skills; ability to build relationships with senior stakeholders and effectively influence across a complex stakeholder environment
Ability to engage with and inspire technical teams
An ability to break constraints and get things done, including a willingness to roll-up your sleeves and ‘pitch in’ where required
Additional Information

Perks and benefits

At SEEK we offer:

Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role
SEEK is committed to operating sustainably and is preparing for the impacts of climate change and the transition to a low-carbon future, and is working to minimise its environmental impacts which includes a long-term emissions reduction target of net zero by FY2050
The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year
Frequent events including sports days, year-end party, hackathon, and trivia
Casual dress every day

At SEEK, we are passionate about fostering a culture of inclusion and wellbeing that embraces and values the diversity of our people. We are a purpose driven business that works with heart.

We know teams with diverse ideas, experiences and perspectives are more creative and are critical to ensuring effective delivery and innovating to enable our future success. As such, we welcome applications from people with diverse backgrounds and life experiences, especially as they relate to gender, sexual identity, culture, faith, disability and life stages. If you have the skills, curiosity and an adaptable mindset but don't meet every responsibility or qualification listed in this advertisement, please still get in touch with us. Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.

For this role, only those with eligible right to work will be considered.

SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees.

Ad Text:
Senior Change Management Analyst

V/Line’s purpose is to connect Victorians through safe, reliable, and accessible transport. We believe in giving all Victorians opportunities through travel and transport – connecting them to jobs, education, family and friends, services, tourism and trade.

V/Line is experiencing significant growth and we’re delivering more services, more trains, cheaper fares, and huge projects. With more than 3700 weekly train and coach services, an expansive freight network and unprecedented rail investment, millions of Victorians depend on us to deliver. You could be one of our 2700 committed team members who are up to the challenge.

About the Role

As the Senior Change Management Analyst, you’ll guide and support V/Line managers and teams through a long-term change program that is embedding an asset management culture of continuous improvement.

This program includes the driving adoption and uptake of V/Line’s ISO 55001 certified Enterprise Asset Management Framework (EAMF) so that it becomes business as usual. This position plays a key role in guiding the change activities that ensure continued maintenance of V/Line’s ISO 55001 certification and maturity uplift targets.

You will apply structured change management methodologies to plan, implement, and monitor change activities from strategic to operational levels. Acting as a trusted advisor, you’ll influence stakeholders, develop communication strategies, and deliver training and awareness programs that help people thrive through change.

Key accountabilities include:

Develop and implementing strategies or plans for driving adoption and update of the EAMF and its continuous improvement.

Assess change risks and develop strategies or plans to mitigate resistance.

Assist in coordinating program planning, monitoring, and communication activities.

Lead stakeholder engagement and deliver targeted communications campaigns.

Coach leaders and managers to champion change and support their teams effectively.

About You

The ideal candidate is a proactive and adaptable change professional who understands how people navigate change, with exceptional communication skills and the ability to influence at all levels. They’ll have the capability to deliver meaningful outcomes in a complex environment.

Our ideal candidate brings:

Strong knowledge of change management principles, methodologies, and tools.

Experience in planning and implementing change in asset intensive or operational environments.

Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills.

Ability to coach leaders and build capability across the organisation.

Relevant qualifications in business, engineering, or change management (postgraduate and certifications highly regarded).

Demonstrated alignment with V/Line’s values of responsiveness, integrity, impartiality, accountability, respect, leadership and human rights.

If your skills or experience don’t exactly match our listed requirements, we still encourage you to apply. We value diverse perspectives and believe in the potential for growth and development.

Why V/Line

In addition to free myki travel, we offer:

Community impact – Make a genuine difference. Work in a role that connects Victorians, every day.

Huge potential – We’re transforming, and you can too. Be a change maker, recognised for your contribution and creativity.

Dynamic environment – V/Line operates in a constantly changing space. Join a fast-paced and exciting organisation.

Collaborative team – You’ll be part of a broader supportive team. Surround yourself with talented, passionate peers.

Flexible working – We support flexible working. Work in a way that supports you to thrive in your role.

We are committed to ensuring a comfortable and accessible recruitment experience. If you need any adjustments or have specific accessibility requirements at any stage of the process, please contact our Talent team at TalentSupport@vline.com.au or 1800 800 007 for confidential support.

As an equal opportunity employer, V/Line is committed to creating a diverse, inclusive and respectful workplace and network that reflects the communities we serve. We accept and value the contributions of all our employees regardless of gender, ethnicity, sexual orientation, religion, age or disability. We were also named a Work 180 endorsed employer for the second year in a row – meaning, we are committed to creating a great workplace for women.

We proudly acknowledge First Peoples of Victoria. We acknowledge their ongoing strength in practicing the world’s oldest living culture. We acknowledge the Traditional Owners’ lands, waters, and skies on which we live and pay respects to their Elders past and present.

At V/Line, safety is our priority. Successful applicants will undergo relevant pre-employment and medical checks to meet our safeworking standards. V/Line is also a proud Child Safe employer. 

Applications close: 19th of January 2026.

Job Description

At SEEK, we’re on a mission to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives, and to help organisations succeed. Data is at the heart of how we do this — powering experimentation, personalisation, and intelligent product experiences used by millions across Asia-Pacific every day.

We’re looking for a Senior Analytics Engineer to join our Experimentation team — a pivotal role within SEEK’s AI & Analytics Data Products ecosystem. This role sits at the intersection of data engineering, experimentation methodology, and analytics, helping SEEK make evidence-based decisions at scale. SEEK uses a best-in-class experimentation platform, with this role contributes to building the data pipelines, models, and analytics layer that make experimentation trustworthy, scalable, and actionable.

The Role

As a Senior Analytics Engineer, you’ll build the trustworthy, scalable data assets that underpin SEEK’s experimentation and product analytics. You’ll transform raw data into well-modelled, documented, and tested datasets that data scientists and analysts can rely on to measure impact and drive insight.

You’ll work side-by-side with data scientists, platform engineers, and product teams to bring experiments to life — designing pipelines, solving data challenges, and shaping the analytics and data layer of SEEK’s experimentation platform.

This role blends technical depth with real business impact — perfect for someone who loves working with data that actively powers decisions, not just describes them. What 

Qualifications

What You’ll Do

Design, develop, and operate scalable SQL and dbt models for experimentation data (assignment, exposure, and outcomes).
Build reliability and observability into every dataset through validation frameworks, monitoring, and continuous improvement.
Partner with data scientists to enable trustworthy experiment analysis and design.
Shape SEEK’s experimentation platform, implementing scalable data models and metric frameworks.
Investigate and resolve data issues, identifying root causes and implementing lasting fixes.
Document, govern, and communicate — ensuring data assets are understood, accessible, and fit for purpose.
Lead by example, mentoring team members and contributing to analytics engineering craft and standards.
Collaborate across SEEK, engaging with central Data teams to align practices, tools, and best-in-class engineering standards.

About You
You’re passionate about high-quality data, strong engineering fundamentals, and the role analytics plays in shaping product strategy. You enjoy solving complex data problems and thrive in a collaborative, cross-functional environment.


You’ll Bring:
Advanced SQL skills and experience building production-grade data transformations.
Strong dbt experience (or equivalent) with focus on testing, reliability, and scale.
Experience working in cloud-based data environments (e.g. Databricks, Snowflake, or BigQuery).

Working knowledge of Python or PySpark for analysis or data validation.
Solid grasp of analytics engineering practices — version control, documentation, testing, and quality.
Statistical literacy to support experiment design and data validation.
Ability to translate analytical and experimentation needs into robust, well-modelled data assets.
Excellent communication skills and a collaborative mindset.
Confidence in leading technical design discussions, mentoring peers, and contributing to best practice evolution.

Bonus Points For:
Experience with experiment data, assignment and metrics pipelines.
Familiarity with Tealium, Segment, or other tracking systems.

Exposure to CI/CD for analytics (e.g. automated testing, dbt deployments).
Experience contributing to shared data infrastructure or governance initiatives.
Additional Information

The Team
You’ll report to SEEK’s Head of Experimentation and collaborate daily with:

Peers: Data Scientists, Data Engineers, Tracking Specialists, Analysts
Key Partners: AI Platform Services, Product Analytics, Product Management

Together, you’ll continue building SEEK’s evolving SEEK’s experimentation capabilities — enabling faster, more confident decision-making across the business.

Tailored career development planning 
Professional development sessions with industry leading guest speakers

Key Duties

Apply advanced data mining, machine learning and statistical techniques to structured and unstructured data.

Job title: EL1 Data Scientist (Senior Data Scientist)
Rate: $81.81 to $89.84 per hour, plus super (37.5 hours per week)
Contract: 12 months, with extension option up to 6 months
Start date: Early to mid February 2026

About Us
Canberra Consulting delivers highly skilled professionals to Government and Defence clients. We back our consultants with clear briefs, responsive communication, and a practical, high-trust approach that helps you do your best work.

The Opportunity
We are seeking an EL1-level Data Scientist for a Canberra based Australian Government engagement. You will partner with business and technical stakeholders to define problems, source and prepare data, build and validate models, and translate complex analysis into decision-ready recommendations. This role is suited to someone who is hands-on with modelling, confident communicating with non-technical stakeholders, and comfortable operating in a governed environment where quality, transparency, privacy, and security obligations matter. You will also contribute to capability uplift through knowledge sharing and coaching, helping build stronger analytics practice across the team.

Key Responsibilities
Apply advanced data mining, machine learning, and statistical techniques to structured and unstructured data.
Build, validate, and deploy predictive and explanatory models to address business problems and inform decision making.
Provide insights into drivers of business performance and influence priorities through evidence-based recommendations.
Engage business areas to understand requirements and translate complex analytical concepts into clear, actionable outputs.
Assess and select modelling techniques and data sources, ensuring data quality, integrity, and security across the analytics lifecycle.
Present technical and non-technical information clearly and concisely, tailored to stakeholder needs.

Behavioural capabilities

Excellent written and verbal communication, including the ability to present complex information to a range of audiences.
Proven ability to manage competing priorities and deliver high-quality outcomes under tight timeframes.

Security Clearance
You must be an Australian Citizen and hold a minimum Baseline security clearance. Successful candidates may also be required to obtain an ACIC organisational suitability assessment.

The Opportunity

We are looking for an entrepreneurial and strategic executive to join our leadership team. This role will drive new revenue growth for DCA, leverage existing expertise, develop new service offerings and identify external partnerships to deliver on DCA’s strategic objectives.

This is a dynamic and exciting new opportunity to help grow the DCA’s influence through collaboration with members, government and peak bodies, helping to build the sustainability of DCA through diversified revenue streams, new offerings and strategic alliances.




What You’ll Do

Deliver a comprehensive partnerships strategy and framework, setting out growth and revenue targets

Identify opportunities for strategic alliances and partnerships with peak bodies, research institutions and other subject matter experts to enhance DCA’s reputation and capability

Develop detailed business cases for future investment opportunities, such as consulting services for members based on quantitative and qualitative data and research

Use data and insights to strengthen member value proposition through new commercial offerings

Develop DCA’s social impact plan and articulate the alignment of D&I with ESG

Partner with departments across DCA to identify new opportunities to commercialise existing capabilities and products to develop new revenue streams.




What We’re Looking for

15+ years’ experience in strategy development and execution, partnerships and stakeholder engagement

Proven success in developing detailed business plans and generating income streams through strategic partnerships

Deep understanding of the consulting life cycle and processes

Experience with evaluation and monitoring frameworks to develop and adapt offerings to consistently meet stakeholder needs

Knowledge of ESG and social impact frameworks

Proactive and adaptable mindset with the ability to quickly build strong and trusted relationships with key stakeholders

Strong relationship-building and communication skills, with a talent for tailoring engagement to diverse audiences

Analytical mindset to translate data into practical solutions and actionable insights

Strong understanding of diversity and inclusion, and a willingness to grow and learn




About Diversity Council Australia

Diversity Council Australia (DCA) is the nation’s leading independent peak body for diversity and inclusion. We are a member-based, not-for-profit, with a strong network of around 1,300 member organisations, including some of Australia’s largest employers. For over 40 years we have been at the forefront of helping shape more equitable workplaces, contributing to a stronger economy and fairer society.

Our evidence-led approach is centred on lived experience, and our research consistently shows that inclusive organisations are more innovative, productive, and resilient in changing environments.

Through groundbreaking research, practical tools, events, advocacy, education and training, we provide expert guidance across a spectrum of diversity dimensions to employees, leaders, policymakers and the broader community. We equip organisations with the tools and insights they need to champion the undeniable benefits of diversity and inclusion. This work also supports our charitable purpose, which is to promote and advance diversity and inclusion in workplaces for the benefit of individuals, organisations and the broader community.

Our vision is to create a just and equitable Australian society where people in all their diversity can thrive.

Our learning culture unites us as a team and sets the tone of our working environment.

DCA values lived experience as well as expertise, and we encourage applications from people with Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander backgrounds, who have caring responsibilities, from culturally and racially marginalised groups, people with disability, people who experience ageism, LGBTIQ+ people, and people who experience exclusion because of their social class. For more information explore dca.org.au




Why join us?

Be part of a purpose-led organisation driving real change across Australian workplaces.

Flexible working arrangements and a values-aligned culture. Truly hybrid environment.

Nationally recognised thought leader in diversity, equity and inclusion.

A leadership role with room for creativity, innovation and influence.

Salary sacrificing.

Increased Superannuation.

Professional development opportunities and budget.

12 weeks gender neutral parental leave and flexi-leave options.




Apply now:

If you’re ready to lead transformative work that makes a difference, we’d love to hear from you. Submit your resume and a brief cover letter outlining your suitability for the role via the Seek Apply Now prompts.

If you don’t tick every box in the relevant experience or skills required section, please don’t rule yourself out. Research suggests that women and other people in underrepresented groups tend to only apply if they meet every requirement. We focus on hiring people who share our values of Inclusion, Growth Mindset, Fortitude, Excellence and Collaboration, rather than ticking all the boxes – so if this role resonates with you, please apply.

Job Title: Technical (Data) Business Analyst - Contract - 6 months - Brisbane
Ad Text:
Our client  is seeking a Technical Business Analyst to support their ongoing Data Modernisation projects on a 6 Month Contract - starting in January 2026  This role offers an exciting opportunity to work at the intersection of business and technology, ensuring solutions meet the evolving needs of the organisation.

Location: Brisbane, Australia
Type: Contract

Role Overview

We are seeking a Technical Business Analyst to support the migration of on-prem SQL databases to Microsoft Azure. This role sits at the intersection of data engineering, cloud platforms, and business stakeholders, translating complex data and platform requirements into clear, actionable delivery outcomes.

This is a hands-on, technical BA role.

Key Responsibilities

Elicit, analyse, and document functional and non-functional requirements for migrating SQL databases to Azure.

Work with architects and engineers on solutions leveraging:

Azure SQL / Azure Synapse

Azure Data Factory (ADF) for data ingestion and orchestration

Databricks for data transformation and analytics

Translate business and data requirements into:

Data models

Source-to-target mappings

Pipeline and transformation logic

Support Azure DevOps:

Backlog management

User stories, acceptance criteria

Sprint planning and delivery tracking

Lead and coordinate UAT activities:

Define UAT scope, scenarios, and test cases

Support defect triage and resolution

Validate data accuracy, reconciliation, and quality

Act as the bridge between business users, data teams, and cloud engineers, ensuring alignment on outcomes and constraints.

Required Skills & Experience

Strong experience as a Technical Business Analyst in data-centric environments.

Proven experience working on cloud data migrations, ideally from on-prem SQL to Microsoft Azure.

Solid understanding of:

SQL databases (querying, schema, performance concepts)

Azure Data Factory

Databricks

Azure DevOps

Experience documenting:

Data flows

Data transformations

Integration and interface specifications

Hands-on involvement in UAT planning and execution.

Strong stakeholder management across technical and non-technical audiences.

Please only apply if you are able to do 3 days on site in Brisbane each week and able to start in January 2026.

We are a specialist team that partners with leading international researchers and multi-disciplinary teams

Our purpose is to better understand human behaviour & financial decision making

We build on this richer understanding to develop, test, and scale better financial services

Together we can drive the organisation’s purpose to Build a Brighter Future for All

Do work that matters

The Behavioural Science Centre of Excellence is responsible for bringing the latest behavioural science insights and research methods into the CBA Group, and maximising the impact of these insights through rigorous empirical methods. Our team provides a supportive environment to grow as a behavioural science researcher and practitioner. Our work spans across the Group, providing opportunities to work alongside industry-leading User Experience, Data Science, Artificial Intelligence and Strategy teams.

In this role you will be responsible for applying behavioural science to improve everyday financial decisions. You will be responsible for supporting the Group in delivering evidence-based experiences to improve financial decisions, experiences, and outcomes for millions of customers. As the senior behavioural scientist, you are the teams most technical advisor, having the ability to teach and improve the way we approach our empirical toolkit and analysis. This role will report to the Chapter Lead for our Applied Behavioural Science chapter and work closely with other leads from our research unit. The team sits within the Data & Analytics Practice, as part of our Technology Business Unit. The team’s focus is Human-Centered AI, and you will also work closely with our Customer, Digital and AI teams in our Retail Banking Business Unit.

See yourself in our team

CommBank is Australia’s largest bank, serving millions of customers every day. The CommBank Behavioural Science Centre of Excellence was established in 2016 to drive an evidence-based approach in improving the financial wellbeing of customers and communities.

With an emphasis on evidence, experimental methods, and expert collaboration—this team has delivered a range of financial services innovations, leading research outputs, as well as positive business, customer, and community outcomes.

On any given week, in this role you will

Identify opportunities where behavioural science can help improve everyday financial decisions.

Influence senior leaders across the group to adopt Behavioural Science principles and techniques within their cross functional teams to improve decision making processes and strategic initiative outcomes.

Buddy with behavioural scientists across the team, collaborate to curate a cohort of high performing behavioural scientists, and foster a culture of innovation and collaboration. Through this, you will help the team achieve our organisational purpose and continue building a world class Behavioural Science team.

Design and execute large-scale randomised controlled trials. Providing the team with guidance on advanced research methodologies, ensuring robust experimental design, data analysis, and interpretation of results. Specifically tying results back to the business objectives.

Producing and presenting rigorous research outputs. This includes having a strong statistics background, being able to analysis both lab, field, and natural experiments across large datasets.

Representing the organisation at industry conferences and events, contributing to the advancement of behavioural science across different contexts.

Serving as a subject matter expert for business units across the CBA Group

Communicating scientific insights and project outputs to executive leaders and the wider financial services industry

Above all, this opportunity will allow you to have fun and grow within a highly dynamic, collaborative, and innovative work environment.

We are interested to hear from you if you have

Strong familiarity with behavioural science / economics literature. Candidates having worked in Human Centred AI teams across the world will be highly favourable and encouraged to apply.

Strong leadership across peers and interpersonal skills

Strong ability to showcase strategic thinking – translating insights into impact.

Technical understanding of empirical methods used in social sciences (e.g. statistics; econometrics; RCTs)

Professional experience (financial services or management consulting experience is a plus)

Proven track record of delivery, highlighting the role you played as an individual

Project management experience (experience supporting research projects preferred)

Proven ability to communicate scientific insights clearly and concisely to industry audiences

Proven ability to problem solve in a complex large scale organisation

Proven ability to work in cross functional teams, highlighting an ability to influence and showcase how behavioural science was leveraged with multiple toolkits at the table

Demonstrated ability to use statistical programming software (R or Python preferred).

Qualification

Extensive professional experience with Undergraduate or Masters level credential in a behavioural or social science discipline (e.g. psychology, cognitive science, economics, computational social science).

Alternatively, some professional experience with Masters or Doctoral level credential in behavioural and economic science (e.g. psychology, cognitive science, economics, computational social science, neuroscience)

Experience in Human-Centered Artificial Intelligence is highly preferred for this candidate

Working with us

Whether you’re passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career with CommBank is for you.

Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive, and flexible workplace with flexible work locations. One where we’re driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.

Here, you will thrive. You will be supported when faced with challenges and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We’re hiring talent from across all of Australia and have opened technology hubs in Melbourne and Perth. We really love working here, and we think you will too.

**Apply Now to live your best life, by doing your best work with us! **

If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest, x15ventures), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.

We're aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.

Who are we?

Craft your future with Suntory Oceania, a new $3b multi-beverage partnership between Suntory Global Spirits and Suntory Beverage & Food. Underpinned by quality, craftsmanship and a strong sense of purpose, our exciting new partnership will be powered by two manufacturing sites, five distribution centres and more than 1500 Suntorians across Australia and New Zealand.

Our market-leading portfolio will have over 40 brands, including Jim Beam® and Maker's Mark® Bourbon, Hibiki® Japanese Whisky, Canadian Club® Whisky, -196, V Energy, Maximus, and Suntory BOSS Coffee. As One Suntory, we will be positioned as the fourth largest beverage player in the region, ready to ignite the category, creating more beverage moments from sunrise to sunset. Together, we will bring the best of Suntory to Oceania.

 

The Opportunity:

As BI Product Manager, you’ll play a pivotal role in our Analytics, AI & Automation (AAA) capability. You’ll own the Analytics Product layer, translating business needs into scalable, governed, and insight-driven solutions built on Azure, Databricks, and consumed through Power BI.

You’ll partner with business Product Owners, Data Engineering, AI, and Automation teams to define and deliver a clear BI product roadmap that lifts analytics maturity and enables trusted insights at scale.

 

Key Responsibilities:

Shape the BI Strategy: Own and evolve the BI product vision and roadmap aligned to AAA strategy and business priorities.

Deliver Scalable Solutions: Ensure BI products align with Azure and Databricks standards and support advanced analytics use cases.

Stakeholder Engagement: Act as the primary interface between business and technical teams, driving prioritisation and adoption.

Advanced BI Development: Guide the design of high-quality Power BI dashboards and reports, applying strong DAX and SQL skills.

Data Governance: Embed governance, metric consistency, and security into BI products.

Agile Delivery: Manage the BI product backlog and deliver iteratively within Agile frameworks.

Commercial Impact: Ensure BI solutions deliver measurable business value across revenue growth, cost efficiency, and performance.

 

What you need to be successful:

Expertise in Power BI, including advanced DAX and SQL skills.

Strong understanding of Azure and Databricks platforms.

Proven experience in Agile product management and stakeholder engagement.

A data governance mindset and ability to embed trust into analytics products.

Commercial acumen to translate insights into business outcomes.

Desirable:

Knowledge of data engineering, ETL processes, and semantic modelling.

Proficiency in Python or R for advanced analytics.

Aesthetic sense for creating visually compelling dashboards.

Job Title: Senior Analyst - WA Future System Planning & Forecasting
Ad Text:
AEMO at the Heart of Energy 

AEMO is Australia’s independent energy system and market operator and system planner. AEMO’s purpose is to ensure safe, reliable and affordable energy today, and enable the energy transition for the benefit of all Australians.  Australian governments are now committed to a net zero economy for Australia by 2050 and our vision is to enable this. We have the once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to co-design the future of our energy systems, and our core values revolve around character, commitment, and connection. Join us as we contribute to this significant transition in the energy sector.   

About the role 

AEMO’s WA Future System Design & Transformation group is responsible for planning the power system in the context of unprecedented transformation, supporting AEMO’s mission of designing a sustainable energy system that provides affordable, safe and reliable energy for all Australians. 

You will be responsible for supporting the long-term energy outlooks for Western Australia's electricity and gas demand and supply, the Wholesale Electricity Market (WEM) Electricity Statement of Opportunities (ESOO) and the WA Gas Statement of Opportunities (GSOO). These flagship reports support industry in planning for the Energy transition. 

This is a 6-month Fixed Term Contract. The team is based in Perth, with remote working options also available across Adelaide, Brisbane, Canberra and Melbourne offices. 

What you will be doing

Support the development of AEMO's annual flagship publications, the WEM ESOO and the WA GSOO, leading the development of main chapters for publication, such as reliability, supply, demand and consumption.

Collect and analyse data from AEMO teams such as WA System Engineering, WA Operational Planning & Forecasting and WA Distributed Markets.

Collect and analyse data from external stakeholders such as Energy Policy WA, Western Power and industry market participants.

Analyse and model energy demand and supply trends across electricity and gas systems.

Identify and execute on opportunities for improved alignment between the WEM ESOO and WA GSOO publications and AEMO's National Electricity Market ESOO and East Coast GSOO publications. 

What you will bring to the role

Experience in the electricity and gas sectors, with WEM experience preferable but not essential.

Forecasting experience using Excel to handle large volumes of data.

Proficiency with the Microsoft Office suite.

Experience in PowerBI and programming languages such as Python, R and SQL will be highly regarded.

Strong report writing and critical thinking skills.

Professional development via projects, industry networks, job rotation, study assistance and more.

Embrace a healthier you with our wellness program, discounted health insurance, gym perks and our comprehensive Employee Assistance Program (EAP).

24-month fixed term contract
Sydney or Melbourne location
Salary from $152,074 to $163,970 (depending on experience) + 15.4 % superannuation
Applications will close at 11:59pm AEDT, Tuesday 13 January 2026

 

The team 

The Digital, Data & Technology (DD&T) Portfolio Office delivers a broad suite of services in portfolio management, project delivery, business planning, and governance to support ASIC's strategic priorities. We work in close partnership with ASIC IT and the newly established RegistryConnect (RC) program to ensure projects are aligned with both strategic direction and operational needs.

 

The role

As a Senior Business Analysts within the RegistryConnect Program, you will employ diverse business analysis techniques, including agile methodologies, to deliver high-quality project outcomes within established timelines. Your key responsibilities will encompass eliciting, analysing, and managing both high-level and detailed business requirements, conducting enterprise analysis, assessing and validating solutions, and addressing both functional and non-functional requirements.

 

More specifically, you will: 

Collaborate with business SMEs and IT teams to analyse and validate business needs through stakeholder engagement and workshops.
Document business, functional and non-functional requirements in clear, accessible formats using user stories for Agile projects.
Design user interfaces aligned with User Centred Design (UCD) principles and Australian Government accessibility and usability standards.
Develop process maps, including current state analysis and future-state design.
Rapidly understand business structures and strategies to align work with organisational goals.
Support test planning and execution activities.
Assist with UAT preparation, system implementation and development of user guides and training materials.
Demonstrate strong self management and accountability in delivering team and organisational priorities.

 

About you

The ideal candidate this role will be an experienced, proactive and detail-oriented Business Analyst professional who possess strong analytical and communication skills. The ideal candidate will excel at translating complex business needs into clear, actionable requirements and thrive working within a collaborative environment with both business and IT stakeholders. They should also have a strong background in business analysis techniques, including Agile methodologies, Scaled Agile Framework (SAFe) and be adept at delivering high-quality project outcomes within established timelines.

 

 

In addition, you will have:

Relevant tertiary qualifications or professional certifications, with Agile and SAFe certification being highly desirable.
Excellent knowledge of SDLC and Agile methodology.
Strong skills in eliciting, documenting, and managing requirements.
Experienced with industry process modelling and requirements management tools.
Demonstrated technology-based project experience within in large complex enterprise environments.
Exceptional analytical and enterprise-level problem-solving skills in IT systems and complex issue resolution.
Proven ability to independently manage multiple tasks or projects with full accountability for outcomes.
Skilled in delivering professional verbal and written communication to diverse audiences, with a strong commitment to customer service excellence.
Demonstrable experience in integrating different business applications and improving efficiency of workflows and processes.
Strong knowledge and previous experience working with systems and technology such as SAS, Microsoft Dynamics, Java, Siebel/Oracle fusion, Peoplesoft and Data Warehouse, highly desirable.

Dexus (ASX: DXS) is a leading Australasian fully integrated real asset group, managing a high-quality Australasian real estate and infrastructure portfolio valued at $50.1 billion. The Opportunity

As a Senior Finance Analyst, you will support the Retail business through accurate analysis and strategic reporting. The role involves preparing asset plans, maintaining financial models, and partnering with stakeholders to drive decision-making. You'll contribute to portfolio performance, influence management decisions, and continuously improve reporting processes within a collaborative, high-performing team.

What you'll bring to the role

Prepare and maintain financial models to analyze key investment metrics and support strategic decision-making for the retail portfolio.
Review external valuations and collaborate with investment and valuation teams to ensure accuracy and alignment with internal assumptions.
Coordinate and deliver timely, accurate portfolio and fund-level reporting, providing clear explanations and insights.
Partner with stakeholders across the business to deliver meaningful analysis, recommendations, and performance benchmarking.
Drive continuous improvement in reporting processes, systems, and data visualization to enhance efficiency and business outcomes.

About You

Company Description

Nine is Australia’s largest locally owned media company. Working at Nine, you’ll have access to a unique range of experiences and opportunities, helping drive the success of the country’s most trusted television, radio, digital and publishing brands. 

Our content reaches almost every Australian - meaning what we do has real impact. We bring people together, celebrate the big moments, and capture the everyday ones.

Some of our most beloved brands have been part of Australian life for generations, and others - new on the scene - have already found their place firmly in our lives. We’re evolving and we need people like you to bring new ideas, innovate and make your mark.

Job Description

Reporting to the Director of Strategy & Transformation, Streaming & Broadcast, you will provide rigorous data analysis, market research, and project coordination to shape the division’s long-term strategy during this 6-month contract. 

This pivotal role offers the opportunity to influence investment decisions and drive high-impact transformation initiatives across Australia's largest locally owned media company. 

Day to day, you will:

Provide strategic project support and operational alignment for complex, cross-functional initiatives.
Coordinate projects by maintaining trackers and delivering status updates for key initiatives.
Draft high-quality presentation materials and briefing documents for executive stakeholders.
Gather market intelligence and data to drive business cases and the 5-Year Plan.
Document current and future-state processes to support operational transformation and change.
Build financial models to support strategic business cases across Sport, News, and Entertainment.
Research local and global competitors to produce insights on industry trends and benchmarks.
Qualifications

What you'll bring:

Prior experience in strategy, management consulting, or commercial analyst roles within media or tech.
Ability to synthesise analytical work into clear, concise presentations for senior audiences.
Strong skills in analysing complex data sets to identify trends and support decision-making.
Proficiency in financial modelling with a solid understanding of business models and statements.
Adaptability to navigate a fast-paced environment while managing multiple priorities.
A collaborative style with the ability to build effective relationships across diverse teams.
Additional Information

How we work

At Nine, our flexible work options vary by role and team. Depending on the position, this may include flexible hours, hybrid work, or part-time arrangements. We welcome discussing your flexibility needs during the hiring process - just ask the Talent Acquisition team.

18 weeks paid parental leave with no distinction between primary and secondary carers.

Job Title: Data & Testing Lead - Donesafe Implementation / Digital Transformation
Ad Text:
Contract: 6 Months (High potential for extension)  

About Stowe Australia 

Stowe Australia is a leading family owned electrical and communications contractor with a heritage dating back to 1910. As one of Australia's largest electrical contractors with a national footprint and a workforce of over 2,000 employees, the company delivers comprehensive solutions across major projects. Driven by a strong safety culture and a commitment to innovation, Stowe combines over a century of operational excellence with a steady and diverse client base throughout the country. 

The Opportunity 

Stowe Australia is embarking on a major national transformation of our Health, Safety, Environment, and Quality (HSEQ) systems. We are moving away from legacy processes to implement the HSI Donesafe platform across our entire national operation.  To support this program, we’re seeking an experienced Data Analysis & Testing Lead. 

This is a core assurance and is essential to the successful delivery of the program.  This role will own the data quality, extraction, cleansing, validation and end to end UAT making this role a key determinant of whether the platform is safe, accurate, and ready for national deployment.   

This is a hands-on, high-impact contract role where you will work directly with the project team, SMEs, and the vendor to ensure the platform is ready for a successful national rollout. 

The Role 

As the Data & Testing Lead, you will be responsible for: 

Leading data mapping, cleansing, transformation, migration and validation activities 
Developing and implementing end-to-end testing strategies, comprehensive test plans, detailed scripts, and UAT governance  
Coordinating and executing UAT across 25+ Donesafe modules 
Managing defects, retesting and go-live readiness 
Working closely with the HSI Donesafe vendor team and Stowe SMEs 
Supporting documentation, reporting and change readiness activities 
You will be the key technical and Quality Assurance specialist for this transformation program. 

About You 

You are a detail-oriented data specialist with strong testing experience and the confidence to lead a large-scale SaaS implementation. You bring: 

Essential 

5+ years in data analysis, data migration or data governance 
Strong experience leading UAT and functional testing for SaaS/enterprise systems 
Ability to create clear test plans, test cases, scripts and traceability 
Excellent Excel capability (Power Query, XLOOKUP, cleansing, validation) 
Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills 
Ability to work independently and proactively in a fast-paced delivery environment 

Nice to Have 

Experience with HSI Donesafe, HSI Solv, or other HSE/WHS systems (INX, Bsafe etc) 
Background in construction, electrical, mining, field services or compliance industries 
Experience with integrations (API/SFTP), SQL or Power BI 

Why Join This Project? 

Impact: Play a key role in a high profile digital transformation for an industry leader and deliver a platform that will enhance safety and operational excellence across the business 
Influence: You aren’t just inheriting a system; you are helping design it from the ground up to ensure it works for our people.  
Longevity: While this is a 6-month contract, extension is highly likely as we move into national rollout and continuous improvement phases. 

Ready to shape the future of safety at Stowe? 

If you are an experienced Data and Testing professional and wants to apply your skills to a major transformation project, apply now.

Job Title: Solution Delivery Analyst (Clinical) - multiple positions available

Ad Text:
The role: 

Queensland Health recognises that progressing our digital health strategy is an essential part of our ongoing commitment to delivering safe, effective, and accessible healthcare to all Queenslanders.

Queensland Health is currently undertaking several of the largest health ICT programs and projects ever seen in Australia. The largest of these, the Digital Hospital Program (DHP) is a visionary program that continues to enable clinical services and enhance our technological capability by extending the availability of the ieMR into more hospitals and community care venues. The Digital Hospital Program will deliver advanced ieMR to 5 Metro North hospitals over the first 5 years. In parallel Queensland Health will be adding over 2,811 additional hospital beds across the state, with four entirely new hospitals and expansions to 11 already world-class facilities.

Implementing an integrated electronic Medical Record (ieMR) across all public hospitals in Queensland is at the heart of our digital transformation and is essential to delivering care, closer to home.  Already used in numerous facilities today, the ieMR is improving care and patient outcomes by offering Queensland Health clinicians access to real-time clinical information for their patients, at point of care.

A Solution Delivery Analyst (Clinical) plays a critical role in bridging clinical and business needs and IT solutions across eHealth Queensland, providing strategic advice on project direction, facilitate business requirements, use case development, and detailed engagement with clinical and business stakeholders. The role includes mentoring business analysts whilst ensuring effective communication and stakeholder engagement.

Is this opportunity for you?

To perform successfully in this role, you must demonstrate:

Proven experience working in a clinical digital transformation designing or redesigning workflows, processes in a healthcare system.
Ability to lead and manage multiple large stakeholder and clinical groups to achieve positive outcomes.
Proven experience in setting the direction for and leading business analysis activities, and in clinical digital transformation process redesign and business case development activities in the health care industry, and intimate knowledge of healthcare processes specifically those used for clinical digital transformation.
Experience overseeing, managing and defining business analysis and process modelling activities for large scale complex organisations.
Proven excellent negotiation, consultation, facilitation and effective written and oral communication skills for use in complex program/ project environment. 
Highly developed ability to manage staff and build client focused and effective teams providing high-quality services to clients

The following experience will be highly regarded:

Strong knowledge and prior experience working across ieMR in a clinical healthcare environment.

While experience in health care is not a mandatory requirement, we highly value candidates who have demonstrated relevant experience in clinical systems, health IT, or digital health. If your experience is in other sectors, please make sure to outline how your knowledge can transfer to the healthcare context.

To be considered for this exciting opportunity submit your CV or resume and a short statement (maximum 2 pages) addressing your experience in each of the key areas outlined above.

About eHealth Queensland:

eHealth Queensland is one of the largest Information Communication Technology operations in the state. It is responsible for ensuring the smooth operation of information systems and technologies so that Queensland Health employees and health providers have access to information that supports the delivery of health care.

Benefits of working with eHealth Queensland:

By joining eHealth Queensland you will work within a fast-paced, challenging and supportive environment where every employee plays a critical role in our ongoing success. 

You will enjoy a variety of benefits, including:

Competitive salary + generous superannuation and leave loading
Flexible working arrangements
Diverse work culture
Career training and development

To apply for this exciting opportunity, submit your resume and a short statement (maximum 2 pages) on how your experience, abilities, knowledge and personal qualities are relevant for the role, taking into account the key responsibilities and attributes noted in the ‘How you will be assessed' section of the role description.
